•   { N ≥ 0 } S { Inv }

(1) S = ? // S = x,n:= E,F // S = x,n:= 1,0

(2) E = ? // E = 0

(3) F = ? // F = 0

≡   Hoare triple

    N ≥ 0 ⇒ wp.(x,n:= E,F).Inv

≡   Prove ⇒

    •   wp.(x,n:= E,F).Inv

    (4) N ≥ 0

    ≡   Assignment

        E = fib.F ∧ 0 ≤ F ∧ F ≤ N

    ≡   Assumption (3)

        E = fib.0 ∧ 0 ≤ 0 ∧ 0 ≤ N

    ≡   ≤ reflexive; Assumption (4)

        E = fib.0

    ≡   Definition of fib

        E = 0 -- Assumption (2)

    ■

⋯   true

■